<subSubSection pageId="212" pageNumber="213" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="212.[151,1437,295,573]" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,418,332,357]" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">
Status at 
<collectingRegion box="[262,412,332,357]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
.
</emphasis>
Recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[601,740,332,357]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
in original description by Allen 
<emphasis box="[1108,1157,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">et al</emphasis>
. (2015: 24). The species was previously known from Papua New Guinea as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Snyder" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[750,929,367,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chrysiptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rex">
<emphasis box="[750,929,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Chrysiptera rex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(non Snyder, 1909); a video of a specimen taken at Tungelo Island, off southeastern New Hanover, at 
<quantity box="[816,902,404,429]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" unit="m" value="24.5" valueMax="46.0" valueMin="3.0">3–46 m</quantity>
depth, St. KR104, in 2014 (identified by Barry C. Russell).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="212" pageNumber="213" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="212.[151,1437,295,573]" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,503,476,501]" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[513,661,476,501]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
: 1, 2.—General distribution: Halmahera (eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1343,476,501]" name="Indonesia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
) east to 
<collectingCountry box="[151,246,512,535]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
, south to 
<collectingRegion box="[360,492,511,536]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[509,615,511,536]" name="Australia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">Australia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[682,862,511,536]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. Found on inshore rocky substrates, 
<quantity box="[1285,1358,511,536]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" unit="m" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6 m</quantity>
depth. Marine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
